`need_update()` is `version_db->version.load() != version` (line 507) and `initializeColumnNames` stores the new version (line 730). So for `for(...) { insert.run(...); select.all(); }` the SELECT re-runs the whole column-name/Structure build each iteration instead of hitting the cached `_structure` fast path at line 1996.

